NEWS file for sparseHessianFD package

VERSION 0.2.0 (Jan. 9, 2015)

   o  Essentially a complete re-write of the package.
   o  New vignette, using a binary choice model as an example.
   Functions for this model are in binary.R.  Access sample simluated
   data with data(binary).
   o  Documentation written using roxygen2
   o  Added unit tests
   o  Core class has been renamed sparseHessianFD. Construction and
   initialization are now two seaprate steps.
   o  New function sparseHessianFD.new is a wrapper around the
   construction and initialization steps.

   Deprecated functions in Version 0.2.0

   o  new.sparse.hessian.object.  Use sparseHessianFD.new instead.
   o  Coord.to.Sym.Pattern.Matrix. Use Coord.to.Pattern.Matrix
   instead, with option symmetric=TRUE.
   o  Sym.CSC.to.Matrix.  Use the spMatrix function in the Matrix
   package instead.
   


VERSION 0.1.1 (Nov. 5, 2013)

   o  Removed functions for sampling from, and computing the density of,
      a multivariate normal distribution.  These functions are now available
      in the sparseMVN package.


VERSION 0.1.0 (Nov. 5, 2012)

   o  Initial upload to CRAN.

